from PIL import Image, ImageEnhance


def adjust_saturation(color, factor):
    image = Image.new("RGB", (1, 1), color)
    enhancer = ImageEnhance.Color(image)
    adjusted_image = enhancer.enhance(factor)
    # Extract the adjusted RGB color
    adjusted_color = adjusted_image.getpixel((0, 0))
    # Convert RGB to HEX
    return "#{:02x}{:02x}{:02x}".format(*adjusted_color)

# VISUALIZATION
post_types = list(postsTypes.index)
post_values = list(postsTypes.values)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
colors = plt.get_cmap('Set2').colors
explode = [0.15 if post_type in ['sticker', 'voice']
           else 0 for post_type in post_types]

# Create the pie chart without labels on the chart
wedges, _, autotexts = plt.pie(
    post_values,
    labels=[None] * len(post_types),  # No labels directly on the pie chart
    autopct='%1.1f%%',
    startangle=140,
    colors=colors[:len(post_types)],
    explode=explode,
    shadow=True,
    pctdistance=0.85,
)

# Add percentage text on wedges
for autotext in autotexts:
    autotext.set_fontsize(10)
    autotext.set_color("black")

# Customize the legend to include both counts and percentages
total = sum(post_values)
legend_labels = [
    f"{post_type} - {value:,} ({value / total:.1%})" for post_type, value in postsTypes.items()]
plt.legend(wedges, legend_labels, title="Post Types",
           loc="center left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))

# Add title
plt.title("Types of Posts", pad=20)

data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'])


def count_posts_including_ukra(year):
    january_posts = data[(data['date'].dt.year == year)
                         & (data['date'].dt.month == 1)]

    count = january_posts['message'].str.contains(
        "", case=False, na=False).sum()

    return count


unique_years = data['date'].dt.year.unique()

for year in unique_years:
    count = count_posts_including_ukra(year)
    print(f"Number of posts including '' in January {year}: {count}")

# VISUALIZATION
ukra_counts = {year: count_posts_including_ukra(year) for year in unique_years}

years = list(ukra_counts.keys())
counts = list(ukra_counts.values())

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
plt.plot(years, counts, marker='o', color='pink',
         linestyle='-', linewidth=2, markersize=8)
plt.title("Number of Posts Including '' in January Each Year")
plt.xlabel("Year")
plt.ylabel("Number of Posts")
plt.grid(True)

# Annotate each point with the count
for i, count in enumerate(counts):
    plt.text(years[i], counts[i] + 5, str(count), ha='center', color='black')

plt.show()

16.1. In this task I created and analyzed biagrams for word pairs for post 16 containing 'ukra' in January each year. Additionaly, create a digram that illustrates 20 the most frequent bigrams that appear in posts containing the substring "". Each bar represents a bigram, and the height of the bar corresponds to the number of times that bigram appears in the filtered dataset.

#Task: Top 20 Bigrams in Posts Containing '' in January each year
In[]:
data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'])
january_posts = data[(data['date'].dt.month == 1) &
                     data['message'].str.contains('', case=False, na=False)].copy()


def preprocess_text(text):
    # Remove punctuation, lowercase
    text = re.sub(r'[^\w\s]', '', text.lower())
    return text.split()  # Tokenize into words


january_posts.loc[:, 'cleaned_message'] = january_posts['message'].apply(
    preprocess_text)


def generate_bigrams(tokens):
    return list(zip(tokens, tokens[1:]))


all_bigrams = []
for tokens in january_posts['cleaned_message']:
    all_bigrams.extend(generate_bigrams(tokens))

bigram_counts = Counter(all_bigrams)
print("Total number of bigrams:", len(bigram_counts))

# Convert to DataFrame for analysis
bigram_df = pd.DataFrame(bigram_counts.items(), columns=[
                         'Bigram', 'Frequency']).sort_values(by='Frequency', ascending=False)

# Step 4: Visualize top 20 bigrams
top_bigrams = bigram_df.head(20)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar([' '.join(bigram) for bigram in top_bigrams['Bigram']],
        top_bigrams['Frequency'], color='skyblue')
plt.title("Top 20 Bigrams in Posts Containing '' in January each year")
plt.xlabel("Bigrams")
plt.ylabel("Frequency")
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Total number of bigrams: 1077396

data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'])
ukrainian_posts = data[data['message'].str.contains(
    '', case=False, na=False)].copy()

# Modify 'year' explicitly
ukrainian_posts.loc[:, 'year'] = ukrainian_posts['date'].dt.year

most_viewed_per_year = ukrainian_posts.loc[
    ukrainian_posts.groupby('year')['views'].idxmax()
]


def shorten_text(text, limit=360, indent_limit=130):
    if len(text) > limit:
        text = text[:limit] + "..."
    if len(text) > indent_limit:
        lines = []
        for i in range(0, len(text), indent_limit):
            lines.append(text[i:i+indent_limit])
        return '\n'.join(lines)
    return text


most_viewed_per_year['message'] = most_viewed_per_year['message'].apply(
    shorten_text
)


def human_readable_number(num):
    if num >= 1e6:
        return f"{num/1e6:.2f}M"
    elif num >= 1e3:
        return f"{num/1e3:.2f}K"
    return str(int(num))


most_viewed_per_year['views'] = most_viewed_per_year['views'].apply(
    human_readable_number
)

# Select relevant columns
most_viewed_per_year_result = most_viewed_per_year[
    ['date', 'message', 'views']
]

print(tabulate.tabulate(most_viewed_per_year_result,
      headers="keys", tablefmt="fancy_grid"))

def get_post_with_most_views_in_january_including_ukra(year):
    january_posts = data[(data['date'].dt.year == year)
                         & (data['date'].dt.month == 1)]
    january_posts = january_posts[january_posts['message'].str.contains(
        "", case=False, na=False)]

    if january_posts.empty:
        return None

    postID = january_posts['views'].idxmax()
    post = january_posts.loc[postID]

    return post

def get_post_with_most_views_in_january_including_ukra(year):
    jan_posts = data[(data['date'].dt.year == year)
                     & (data['date'].dt.month == 1)]
    posts_with_ukra = jan_posts[jan_posts['message'].str.contains(
        "", case=False, na=False)]
    if posts_with_ukra.empty:
        return None
    return posts_with_ukra.loc[posts_with_ukra['views'].idxmax()]

def get_post_with_most_views_including_ukra_by_month(year, month):
    posts_in_month = data[(data['date'].dt.year == year)
                          & (data['date'].dt.month == month)]
    posts_with_ukra = posts_in_month[posts_in_month['message'].str.contains(
        "", case=False, na=False)]
    if posts_with_ukra.empty:
        return None
    else:
        return posts_with_ukra.loc[posts_with_ukra['views'].idxmax()]


# Get unique years
unique_years = sorted(data['date'].dt.year.unique())

# Initialize a list to collect records
records = []

# Loop through each year and month to get the posts
for year in unique_years:
    for month in range(1, 13):
        post = get_post_with_most_views_including_ukra_by_month(year, month)
        if post is not None:
            records.append({
                'year': year,
                'month': month,
                'date': post['date'],
                'views': post['views'],
                'message': post['message']
            })
        else:
            # No post for this month
            records.append({
                'year': year,
                'month': month,
                'date': None,
                'views': 0,
                'message': 'No post'
            })

# Create a DataFrame from the records
df_posts = pd.DataFrame(records)

# Pivot the DataFrame to create a heatmap-friendly format for views
pivot_views = df_posts.pivot(
    index='year', columns='month', values='views').fillna(0)

# Set month names for better readability
month_names = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun',
               'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']
pivot_views.columns = month_names

# Visualize the views using a heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.heatmap(pivot_views, annot=True, fmt=".0f", cmap="YlGnBu", cbar=True)
plt.title("Views of the Most Viewed Posts Containing '' Each Month by Year")
plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Year")
plt.show()

data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'])


def count_posts_including_ukra_by_month(year):
    year_posts = data[data['date'].dt.year == year]
    monthly_counts = (
        year_posts[year_posts['message'].str.contains(
            "", case=False, na=False)]
        .groupby(year_posts['date'].dt.month)
        .size()
    )

    # Fill in missing months with 0
    monthly_counts = monthly_counts.reindex(range(1, 13), fill_value=0)

    return monthly_counts


unique_years = data['date'].dt.year.unique()


# VISUALIZATION
monthly_counts_df = pd.DataFrame()

for year in unique_years:
    counts = count_posts_including_ukra_by_month(year)
    monthly_counts_df[year] = counts

monthly_counts_df = monthly_counts_df.T
monthly_counts_df.columns = [

data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'])
data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

most_forwarded_posts = []
for year, group in data.groupby('year'):
    most_forwarded_from_id = group['_from_id'].value_counts().idxmax()
    most_forwarded_post = group[group['_from_id']
                                == most_forwarded_from_id].iloc[0]

    post_info = {
        "year": year,
        "post_id": most_forwarded_post['id'],
        "message": most_forwarded_post['message'],
        "date": most_forwarded_post['date'],
        "_from_id": most_forwarded_from_id
    }
    most_forwarded_posts.append(post_info)


print("The messages of the posts that were forwarded from another channels the most each year are:")
for post in most_forwarded_posts:
    print(f"Year: {make_bold(post['year'])}, Post ID: {
        post['post_id']}, Date: {make_bold(post['date'])}\n")
    print(f"Message: {post['message']}")
    print("-" * 50)
